{"key":"processedPost-11951081","value":{"id":11951081,"first":11949176,"last":11951967,"when":1265171020,"utime":"02/03/10 06:23 AM","content":"There's lots of fucking around in this thread, but most of it is bullshit.&nbsp; If you're just starting out, you'll be fine around the spores.&nbsp; It takes a few years of exposure for your body to start rejecting the spores and making you sick.&nbsp; Once that happens, you'll be stuck putting on a respirator just to check on your crop and you'll not be able to grow indoors at all, at least not where you live.&nbsp; As said above, I get deathly ill from exposure to <i>H ulmarius</i> spores, and had to give up growing them.<br />It's always best to avoid exposure to the spores before you develop an allergy, if you plan on being around the hobby for very long.&nbsp; In addition, quality of the fruits declines rapidly once they drop spores, so that's another reason to pick prior to or just as the veil breaks.<br />RR","title":"Re: ARE SPORES DANGEROUS?"}}